# VoteChain Blockchain Rules

Smart contracts at `blockchain/` for tamper-proof vote recording on Ethereum.

## Stack

- **Ethereum**
- **Solidity** (^0.8.x)
- **Ganache** — local development and unit testing
- **Sepolia Testnet** — final demonstration and staging

## Environments

| Environment | Network | Purpose |
|-------------|---------|---------|
| Development | Ganache (local) | Contract development, Hardhat/Truffle tests |
| Demo | Sepolia Testnet | Final year project demonstration |

- Never deploy production secrets to Sepolia — use test wallets and test ETH only.

## On-Chain Data Policy

Smart contracts must **never** store:

- Passwords
- CNIC / national ID numbers
- Facial data or biometric templates
- Images (any format)
- Emails, names, phone numbers, or addresses
- Any other personally identifiable information

Smart contracts may **only** store:

- Election ID
- Candidate ID
- Hashed voter identifier (keccak256 — never raw identity)
- Timestamp
- Transaction status

Also permitted: transaction references (tx hash, block number) and election contract addresses.

All voter identity verification happens off-chain via the AI service and MongoDB. The backend relayer submits hashed payloads — contracts never receive raw voter data.

## Contract Design

- Keep smart contracts **modular** — separate ElectionFactory, Election, and VoteRecorder contracts.
- **Optimize gas usage** — use mappings over arrays where possible, minimize storage writes.
- **Document every contract** — NatSpec comments on all public/external functions.
- Heavy validation (eligibility, duplicate vote checks) belongs **off-chain** in the backend; contracts verify cryptographic proofs only.

## Folder Structure

```
blockchain/
├── contracts/       # Solidity source files
├── scripts/         # Deploy scripts (Ganache / Sepolia)
├── test/            # Contract unit tests
├── deployments/     # Deployment addresses per network
└── hardhat.config.js
```

## Example — NatSpec Documentation

```solidity
/// @title VoteRecorder
/// @notice Records hashed vote submissions for a VoteChain election
/// @dev Only the authorized backend relayer can submit votes
contract VoteRecorder {
    /// @notice Submit a vote hash for an election
    /// @param electionId The election identifier
    /// @param voteHash Keccak256 hash of the off-chain vote payload
    function recordVote(uint256 electionId, bytes32 voteHash) external { ... }
}
```

## Integration

- Backend submits transactions via a dedicated relayer wallet.
- Store returned `txHash` in MongoDB `Votes` collection.
- Flutter displays transaction confirmation using the stored hash — never exposes private keys.
